+# PLAN-STARTER-ADDR1 — Starter Plan offline address guidance smoke checklist
+
+Date: 2026-07-05
+
+This checklist covers the Starter Plan idea flow after offline Places became provider-address-only.
+
+Starter Plan ideas may prefill titles, prompts, suggested times, and online labels, but they must not create fake offline addresses. Every offline Plan stop must be backed by a selected provider address before preview or publish.
+
+## Product invariant
+
+Offline Starter Plan stops are incomplete until the user selects a confirmed provider address.
+
+Required offline payload:
+
+```txt
+mode = local
+googlePlaceId
+formattedAddress
+latitude
+longitude
+locationSource = google_places
+addressValidationStatus = confirmed
+```
+
+Starter idea copy such as `addressPrompt`, `addressPublicText`, place labels, or neighborhood hints can guide the user, but it must not make an offline stop valid.
+
+Online Starter Plan stops are unaffected by offline address search. They require a safe online destination instead:
+
+```txt
+mode = remote
+onlineUrl = http:// or https:// URL
+onlineLabel optional
+```
+
+## Expected UX when offline starter places are incomplete
+
+When the user clicks Continue, Preview, or Create while at least one offline place is missing a confirmed provider address:
+
+1. Continue is blocked.
+2. The user is returned to the editable/build step if needed.
+3. Every incomplete offline place block expands.
+4. The screen scrolls or focuses toward the first incomplete offline place.
+5. The top-level error is shown:
+
+```txt
+Some offline places need an address. Choose a verified address for each offline place, or delete the places you do not want to use.
+```
+
+6. Each incomplete offline place shows this inline copy:
+
+```txt
+Choose a verified address for this place, or delete it.
+```
+
+7. The user can either:
+   - select a provider-backed address, or
+   - delete the unwanted offline starter place.
+
+The UI must not create fake provider IDs, coordinates, or formatted addresses from starter idea content.
+
+## Web smoke checklist
+
+Use a Starter Plan idea with at least two offline places and, if available, at least one online place.
+
+### Missing offline address block
+
+- Open the Starter Plan idea create flow.
+- Do not select any offline addresses.
+- Click Preview/Create.
+- Confirm the flow does not continue.
+- Confirm the top-level error appears exactly once near the editor.
+- Confirm every incomplete offline place expands.
+- Confirm each incomplete offline place shows:
+
+```txt
+Choose a verified address for this place, or delete it.
+```
+
+- Confirm the first incomplete offline place is visible or focused after the click.
+- Confirm online/remote places are not marked with offline address errors.
+
+### Partial completion
+
+- Select a Google/provider-backed address for the first offline place.
+- Leave another offline place incomplete.
+- Click Preview/Create.
+- Confirm the completed place no longer shows the inline offline-address error.
+- Confirm the remaining incomplete offline place expands and receives the inline error.
+- Confirm the top-level error still appears.
+
+### Delete unwanted starter places
+
+- Delete an incomplete offline starter place from the inline error area.
+- Click Preview/Create again.
+- Confirm the deleted place is not required anymore.
+- Confirm the user can continue when every remaining offline place has a provider-backed address and every online place has a valid link.
+
+### Provider-backed address success
+
+- For every remaining offline place, search at least three characters and select a Google/provider result.
+- Confirm the selected address appears in the place block.
+- Confirm the form sends a confirmed provider payload.
+- Click Preview/Create.
+- Confirm the flow continues.
+
+### Manual/free-text address regression
+
+- Type or paste manual address-like text without selecting a provider suggestion.
+- Click Preview/Create.
+- Confirm the flow is blocked.
+- Confirm no fake `googlePlaceId`, coordinates, `locationSource`, or `addressValidationStatus` are added by the client.
+
+## Native smoke checklist
+
+Use the same Starter Plan idea shape as the web smoke.
+
+### Missing offline address block
+
+- Open the native Starter Plan idea create flow.
+- Do not select offline addresses.
+- Tap Preview/Create.
+- Confirm the flow does not continue.
+- Confirm the top-level error appears.
+- Confirm every incomplete offline place expands inline.
+- Confirm the first incomplete offline place is scrolled into view as closely as the native list allows.
+- Confirm each incomplete offline place shows:
+
+```txt
+Choose a verified address for this place, or delete it.
+```
+
+- Confirm each incomplete place offers an address picker path and a delete/remove action.
+- Confirm online/remote places are unaffected.
+
+### Native completion and delete paths
+
+- Select a provider-backed address for one offline place.
+- Confirm that place's inline error clears.
+- Delete another incomplete offline place.
+- Tap Preview/Create again.
+- Confirm only remaining incomplete offline places are blocked.
+- Complete all required provider-backed addresses.
+- Confirm Preview/Create can continue.
+
+## API safety regression checklist
+
+Frontend guidance is not the final authority. The API must still reject invalid offline Plan payloads.
+
+```txt
+POST /plans with a local/custom Plan stop and only starter prompt/manual address text
+  => reject missing_offline_provider_address
+
+POST /plans with a local/custom Plan stop and fake coordinates but no confirmed provider source
+  => reject missing_offline_provider_address
+
+POST /plans with a local/custom Plan stop and confirmed Google/provider payload
+  => accept
+
+POST /plans with a remote/online Plan stop and valid onlineUrl
+  => accept
+
+POST /plans with a remote/online Plan stop and missing/invalid onlineUrl
+  => reject missing_online_place_destination
+```
+
+## Google Places cost guard checklist
+
+- Address autocomplete only starts after the configured minimum query length.
+- Details are fetched only after a user selects a suggestion.
+- The missing-address error state itself does not call Google.
+- Expanding multiple incomplete offline places does not automatically trigger search/details calls.
+- Deleting incomplete offline starter places does not call Google.
+
+## Non-goals
+
+Do not add any of these as part of this smoke fix:
+
+```txt
+fake saved Places
+fake Google place IDs
+fake latitude/longitude
+stored Static Maps images
+server-side URL preview fetching
+backend relaxation for starter ideas
+```
+
+## Release sign-off
+
+Before marking this flow ready:
+
+- Web smoke passes.
+- Native smoke passes.
+- API safety regression passes.
+- Online Starter Plan stops remain unaffected by offline address errors.
+- No client-side fallback creates provider-looking address data from starter idea text.
